#   CODE-011: bro/BRO.c: fork-drain, read-grow, goto helpers

bro/BRO.c has substantial copy-paste: BROForkSpot/BROForkBe are ~85-line near-twins, the read-into-growable-Bu8 loop appears 4x, scr_goto/bro_goto have identical bodies, the goto-line clamp is pasted 3x, and bro_has_substr re-rolls u8csFindS. Factor a fork-and-drain helper, a read-grow helper, a goto emitter and a clamp, and reuse abc.

##  Issues

Twin fork helpers, a 4x read-grow loop, twin goto emitters, a 3x clamp, a hand substr.

 -  BROForkSpot/BROForkBe (BRO.c:2496/2586) ~85 lines each, near-identical pipe+fork+exec+drain.
 -  read-into-growable Bu8 loop pasted 4x: BRO.c:2538,2631,3220 +.
 -  scr_goto/bro_goto (BRO.c:1346/1365) byte-identical body, differ only in the sink.
 -  goto-line clamp pasted BRO.c:2040,2110,2189; bro_has_substr (2352) = u8csFindS (Sx.h:383).

##  Blockers

None; single-file BRO.c.

##  Planned

One fork-and-drain + one read-grow + one goto-emit + one clamp; substr via abc.

 -  Repro first (§17): bro fork-spot/fork-be drive a child and render; keep behavior.
 -  BROForkChild(bin,argv) for both; BRODrainFd(buf,fd) for the 4 loops.
 -  One goto-emit(sink,row,col); one clamp; bro_has_substr → u8csFindS.

